CHANCEY v. BAUER et al. No. 8704. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. July 19, 1938. For former opinion, see 97 F.2d 293.

Before FOSTER, SIBLEY, and HUT-CHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

As neither of the judges who concurred in the judgment of the court in the above numbered and entitled cause is of opinion that the petitions for rehearing should be granted, it is ordered that the said petitions be, and the same hereby are, denied.
